-- Deliberately lint-violating fixture for the `medaka_lint` MCP tool golden
-- gate (#249). test/ fixtures are excluded from the pre-commit lint hook
-- (they violate style on purpose), so this file is safe to commit as-is.
--
-- `isDifferent` triggers exactly ONE finding: rule-not-eq (`not (a == b)`
-- should be rewritten `a != b`). `main` calls it so `isDifferent` is
-- reachable (no rule-dead-code finding), and both bindings carry a type
-- signature (no rule-missing-signature finding) — keeping this fixture's
-- expected output to a single, stable finding.
isDifferent : Int -> Int -> Bool
isDifferent a b = not (a == b)

main : Bool
main = isDifferent 1 2
